! Changelog

|!Version |!Date |!Changes |
|v0.1.3 |2026-05-29 |''`application/x-tw-date` storage format changed to 8-char `YYYYMMDD` (local digits, no UTC).'' Bug context: writing a date like "28.01.1900" in a CET locale used to store `19000127230000000` — the local-midnight JS Date got UTC-serialised via `$tw.utils.stringifyDate`, and the 1-hour Berlin offset shifted the calendar day backwards. Date-only fields (birthdays, due-dates, etc.) shouldn't carry that artifact: 28th of January is the 28th of January regardless of timezone. ''(1) New helper `toTwDateOnly(date)`'' in `_date-helpers.js` — extracts LOCAL year/month/day from a JS Date and produces an 8-char `YYYYMMDD` string with no time component and no UTC conversion. `toTwDate` is kept for `application/x-tw-datetime` callers (actual moments in time legitimately need UTC). ''(2) `date.js` scribetype updated.'' `toField` now calls `toTwDateOnly` instead of `toTwDate`. `fromField` unchanged — it goes through `$tw.utils.parseDate` which accepts both 8 and 17 char inputs, so legacy 17-char UTC values written by earlier versions still round-trip cleanly. Wikis self-migrate as users edit each date field. ''(3) Cascade-palette compatibility.'' `cp-firing.js:fireDate` (the +/- arithmetic path) bypasses the scribetype and writes storage form directly; it now dispatches on `item.bindType`: `x-tw-date` → `toTwDateOnly`, `x-tw-datetime` → `toTwDate`. Cascade-palette bumped to 0.0.90 (companion change). ''(4) Tests.'' New specs in `test/scribetypes.js` verify the 8-char output and confirm legacy 17-char input still reads correctly. `twDateOf` helper retained as a "legacy shape" producer; its specs flip from "format expected" to "back-compat path still works". ''(5) Docs.'' `doc/architecture.tid` + `doc/reference.tid` updated to describe the new storage shape. ''Migration note:'' existing 17-char date values in `application/x-tw-date` fields keep displaying correctly via the back-compat read path; rewriting them to 8-char happens lazily as users edit. Manual one-off rewrite is just truncating to the first 8 characters (`19000127230000000` → `19000127` — but careful: the digit truncation gives you the SHIFTED date! Re-enter the value through the UI instead). ''Touches:'' `modules/scribetypes/_date-helpers.js`, `modules/scribetypes/date.js`, `test/scribetypes.js`, `doc/architecture.tid`, `doc/reference.tid`, `plugin.info`, `changelog.tid`. JS modules changed — restart required. |
|v0.1.2 |2026-05-27 |`application/x-string-array` is now TW-list-format-aware: `fromField` formats via `$tw.utils.stringifyList` (wraps space-containing entries with `[[...]]`), `toField` parses via `$tw.utils.parseStringArray` (respects `[[...]]` quoting). On-disk JSON-array format unchanged — only the in-state representation respects quoting now, so multi-word entries (e.g. `Echo Fox`) round-trip cleanly |
|v0.1.1 |2026-05-21 |Two new scribetypes for date round-tripping: `application/x-tw-date` (date-only) and `application/x-tw-datetime` (with `HH:mm`). Smart parser accepts ISO (`YYYY-MM-DD`), German (`DD.MM.YYYY`), shortcuts (`today`, `tomorrow`, `yesterday`), and relative offsets (`±N[d\|w\|m\|y]`). Storage format remains TW's UTC `YYYYMMDDHHmmsssss`. Month arithmetic clamps day-of-month when overflowing |
|v0.1.0 |2026-05-20 |Initial release. `<$scribe>` widget with bidirectional sync of tiddler field (or sub-path inside JSON-encoded field) with state tiddler. Three ship-on type handlers: `text/plain`, `application/json`, `application/x-string-array`. Pattern inspired by Flibbles' `FieldTranscriberWidget` in tw5-graph; this is an independent reimplementation that adds sub-path-into-JSON syncing |
